// The typed capability contract a sandboxed agi-stack tool fulfils.
//
// This is the *contract of record* that replaces the spike's ad-hoc inline WAT
// (02-extensibility.md, ADR-0002/0003): every untrusted third-party / MCP tool
// is a guest that exports this `tool` world, and the host (Wasmtime on
// server/desktop, Wasmi on iOS/browser) imports it through the same WIT, so a
// tool authored once runs on every platform.
//
// The runnable sample in this crate realises the world through the equivalent
// **core-module ABI** (`score: func(param i32) -> i32`), because building a
// full Component Model guest needs `cargo-component` / `wasm-tools`, which the
// scorecard scope (Option A) defers to "designed, noted future". The host
// enforces the same fuel/epoch quotas either way — that is the property that
// actually makes untrusted code safe, and it is proven here today.

package agistack:tool@0.1.0;

/// A relevance scorer — the minimal untrusted-tool shape. The host lowers the
/// JSON envelope (`{ "text": "..." }`) to the input length and lifts the score
/// back into JSON, so the guest stays a pure, side-effect-free numeric kernel.
interface scorer {
    /// Score a text of the given length. Pure: no host imports, no I/O — the
    /// sandbox grants the guest nothing it is not explicitly handed.
    score: func(text-len: u32) -> s32;
}

world tool {
    export scorer;
}
